The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for out-of-distribution detection, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on the analysis of different approaches to estimate various models' epistemic uncertainty and contrast it with extreme value theory based open set recognition. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of generative models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of uncertainty, which is a common topic in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
